text: Tippah River is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Tippah is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "to eat one another", i.e. cannibalism. Variant names are "Tippah Creek" and Tippah River Canal". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Benton County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Marshall County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Tippah County, Mississippi
